In triangle \( \triangle ABC \), it is known that \( AC=3 \) and the three interior angles \( A \), \( B \), and \( C \) form an arithmetic sequence.  
(1) If \( \cos C= \frac {\sqrt{6}}{3} \), find \( AB \);  
(2) Find the maximum value of the area of \( \triangle ABC \).

